      "id": "mother-of-learning-similar",
      "title": "If You Loved Mother of Learning, Read These Next",
      "coverTitle": "Loved\nMother",
      "description": "Time loops, magic academies, and protagonists who actually use their brains.",
      "curatorId": "zorian",
      "curatorNote": "800,000 words of Mother of Learning, and you're still hungry. We know the feeling.\n\nThese eight stories each found their own way into the loop—and their own way to make \"one more cycle\" impossible to resist. Some honor the tradition: magic academies, gradual mastery, conspiracies that unfold across iterations. Others break the mold entirely—a Joffrey redemption epic, a post-apocalyptic comedy, a journal that remembers when the world forgets.\n\nWhat they share isn't a formula. It's the same reward loop MoL perfected: watch someone fail, learn, adapt, and return sharper. Every time.",
      "curatorNoteCN": "读完《Mother of Learning》的80万字，你依然意犹未尽。我们懂这种感觉。\n\n这八本书各自找到了进入循环的方式——也各自找到了让你\"再来一轮\"停不下来的理由。有的走正统路线：魔法学院、渐进式成长、在轮回中层层剥开的阴谋。有的彻底打破模板——Joffrey的救赎史诗、后末世喜剧、一本替你记住被世界遗忘之事的日记。\n\n它们的共同点不是公式，而是MoL锤炼出的那种奖励回路：看一个人失败、学习、适应，然后以更犀利的姿态归来。每一次都是。",
